3 \cdot 2^{2x+2} - 35 \cdot 6^x + 2 \cdot 9^{x+1} = 0
x \in \mathbb{R}
3 \cdot 2^{2x+2} - 35 \cdot 6^x + 2 \cdot 9^{x+1} = 0 \Rightarrow 12 \cdot 2^{2x} - 35 \cdot 2^x \cdot 3^x + 18 \cdot 3^{2x} = 0 \Rightarrow
\Rightarrow 12 \cdot \left(\frac{2}{3}\right)^{2x}-35 \cdot \left(\frac{2}{3}\right)^{x}+18=0 
\left(\frac{2}{3}\right)^{x} = t
2^x=t; ~~3^x=s
12 t^2-35st+ 18s^2=0
(3t-2s)(4t-9s)=0
(2,3)=1
\boxed{x=1~~ \text{or}~~-2}
3\cdot2^x=2 \cdot 3^x ~~\text{or}~~2^{x+2}=3^{x+2}
t
t=\dfrac{35s\pm\sqrt{(-35s)^2-4(12)(18s^2)}}{24}
